data.value:
Advanced column definition rules for data operations:
1. When not empty, the default return is the filled string, ignoring the input of Name/Key;
2. When configured as @sql: starting string, return the SQL query value (first row, first column);
Configuration item supports variable replacement:
1. Sequence parameters @p[n]@, such as @p1@, @p2@;
2. @key ([name]), obtained from input parameters, such as @key (username);
3. @code ([define]), obtained from the defined backend method;
4. @enum ([define]), obtained from the enumeration defined by the site parameters;
5. @dic ([define]), obtained from the dictionary table defined by the server;
6. @para {[define]}, obtained from the site parameter definition;
7. @from ([@table. col]), obtained from the final values of other fields;
8. Other: @empty@ null value, @newfid@ primary key value when adding
When configuring multiple row operations to reset or update, the advanced column only needs to configure filtering conditions

Advanced column definition rules for data acquisition:
1. When not empty, it is recognized as SQL by default. The query results are output based on SQL. If multiple rows or dimension tables are configured, they are output as array objects. Otherwise, the first row and first column values of the SQL query results are returned;
2. When configured as @code (starting string), return the value of the backend method;
3. When configured as sql@code (Starting string, return the value of the backend method as SQL and then query;);
4. When configured as str@code (Starting string, return the value of 'calling the backend method with @val@ as a parameter for the original field value';
5. When configured as @api_ starting string, return the JSON that calls the interface;
6. When configured as @SQL: starting string, it is the same as 1;
Configuration item supports variable replacement:
1. Sequence parameters @p[n]@, such as @p1@, @p2@;
2. @key ([name]), obtained from the output parameter, for example @key(username);
3. @code ([define]), obtained from the defined backend method;
4. @enum ([define]), obtained from the enumeration defined by the site parameters;
5. @dic ([define]), obtained from the dictionary table defined by the server;
6. @para {[define]}, obtained from the site parameter definition;

Filtering rules (generally used for querying or updating):
1、 Filter data using column name=value (default to primary key column as filter column)
1. Definition of columns
(1) By default, the primary key column names are configured on the server (by table);
(2) The component parameter "primary key column name" can overwrite or redefine all configured filtering column names of the component;
(3) Each item in the rule definition can be overwritten by the above definition again. When overwriting the filter column definition, the filter value must also be defined at the same time, such as @p1@, newId
2. Definition of Value
(1) By default, the first sequence parameter is used as the filtering value, i.e. @p1@;
(2) The default primary key value of the component parameter can override or redefine the filtering values for all configurations of the component;
(3) Each item in the rule definition can once again override the above definition, such as @p2@, or for example @key(newId)
Each item defined by the rule can have only filter values defined, or both filter values and filter columns can be defined simultaneously (separated by,), and filter columns cannot be defined separately
2、 Custom filtering criteria
1. Where starting string, for example, where name='@key(user)'and area='@p1@'
3、 Configuration item supports variable replacement:
1. Sequence parameters @p[n]@, such as @p1@, @p2@;
2. @key ([name]), obtained from input parameters, such as @key(username);
3. @code([define]), obtained from the defined backend method;
4. @enum([define]), obtained from the enumeration defined by the site parameters;
5. @dic([define]), obtained from the dictionary table defined by the server;
6. @para{[define]}, obtained from the site parameter definition;
7. @from([@table. col]), obtained from the final values of other fields;
